**Welcome to our image-jam forum!**
This is an experimental space where anyone can create 'themed' or 'collaborative' image threads where anyone can post things in-spirit with the original post. Please be nice, please stay in theme and have fun!

** 1. Search first:** It's likely there's already an existing thread about your theme. Come join us there!
** 2.  Make new threads search-friendly.** If you make a new thread, model your title after existing thread titles for clarity, and include helpful keywords so others can find it easily. (Emoji not required, but appreciated. Discord makes them annoying to add though.) 
** 3. Stay on theme.**

**Have a video suggestion? Please use this channel!**
If you have an idea with sensitive content (or want to remain anonymous), please use <#1062590708093046794>

## Please check No Text To Speech's __YouTube channel__ **before** making a post here, this helps prevent duplicate posts.

**Please stop posting duplicate suggestions. Search for your video suggestion first.**

# **Post Guidelines**
### **Title**
Please make your title descriptive and representative of the video suggestion.
> Low effort titles like "discord scam" and "what is this" may result in your post getting deleted

### **Description**
Please describe your idea in as much detail as possible. These video suggestions are public and we like having multiple people pitch in their ideas.

### **Screenshots / Attachment Rules**
1. No NSFW at all.
2. Censor invite links by putting them inside codeblocks, like this \`discord.gg/ntts\` = `discord.gg/ntts`
3. Screenshots must be on topic

### **How NTTS goes through these**
I use post tags to mark the status of your post. I go through

If your post was deleted, it's because it was low effort, a duplicate, or already covered previously.
channels.name: video-suggestions

Troll posts will be deleted, and you will be blacklisted from viewing the forum.

- **Check to see if your questions have already been answered**
Use the search feature inside of this forum to check if other users have had a similar issue to yours.
You can check the <#1304087278330712178> and <#1342228115245760613>.

- **Do not ping support staff or moderators to answer your questions**
We have lives, we will respond when we are free. This also goes for asking someone in general to answer your question.

Please check this website before posting - https://dontasktoask.com

Foreverably, the developer working on the event, wants feedback specifically from people who are participating in it. Feature ideas and bug reports are only allowed.

## Post Guidelines  Feature Idea
Your feature idea should be clear and specific, it should not benefit you as a person. If the idea is sounding like it benefits you only then it will be denied or altered. Feature ideas should consider everyone, so this can be QoL (Quality of Life), a new command or, a new item.

## Post Guidelines  Bug Report
Bug reports are used for bugs that affect the event entirely, this isn't used for you complaining about "i didn't get the rarest item :(((((((," oh well.
